<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 21-SI SERIES - REPAIR PROCEDURE - DIODE TRIO CHECK</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DIODE TRIO CHECK</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove insulated regulator attaching screw (Item 1,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801711">Figure 11</hotlnk>) to disconnect diode trio (Item 3,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801711">Figure 11</hotlnk>). Lift diode trio from SRE housing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801711" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801711" filename="../figg08/g0801711.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Diode Trio Electrical Check</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. INSULATED ATTACHING SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RECTIFIER BRIDGE STRAPS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DIODE TRIO</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. REGULATOR STRAP</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use ohmmeter to check diode trio (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801711">Figure 11</hotlnk>). Place negative ohmmeter lead on regulator strap and use
                positive ohmmeter lead to check for continuity to each of the three rectifier bridge straps. All three
                readings should indicate continuity. Reverse the ohmmeter leads and perform checks again. Readings
                should all indicate open circuits. On some ohmmeters the polarity of the leads is reversed from above.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If all readings are proper, diode trio is good. If any reading is wrong, replace diode
                trio.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
